    <p>The Sin­ga­pore Demo­cratic Party’s lead coun­sel ar­gued be­fore five judges in the Court of Ap­peal that pub­lic in­ter­est has been de­fined in the Pro­tec­tion from On­line False­hoods and Ma­nip­u­la­tion Act (Pofma) in overly broad terms.</p>
    <p>The On­line Cit­i­zen, which had re­ported on a Malaysian rights group’s claims of un­law­ful ex­e­cu­tion meth­ods by the Sin­ga­pore pris­ons, said it should be enough that it had asked the Min­istry of Home Af­fairs for a re­sponse and in­di­cated in the ar­ti­cle that the claims were al­le­ga­tions.</p>

